OL,3,C'Worse than childbirth': A mother's
OL,4,Cwarning over rising ketamine use
OL,6,FA recovering addict from Kent has
OL,7,Fwarned that the physical pain of
OL,8,Fketamine abuse is "up there" with
OL,9,Fchildbirth, as experts gather in
OL,10,FMargate to tackle a "significant rise"
OL,11,Fin the drug's popularity.
OL,13,FAmy Braid, who is now a mother with a
OL,14,Ffuture she "couldn't have ever
OL,15,Fimagined" during her addiction, shared
OL,16,Fher harrowing experience at a Ketamine
OL,17,FAwareness Day held at the Turner
OL,18,FContemporary gallery.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
